The Security Council has unanimously stepped up sanctions against North Korea since 2006, with the aim of cutting off Pyongyang’s financial channels for the production of ballistic and nuclear missiles.
Mr Pompeo met with North Korea's Rin in the margins of the UN General Assembly and announced that he would visit Pyongyang again next month in preparation for the second summit.
Pompeo has visited North Korea three times this year, but the latest visit was not smooth.
