Ferries can be spotted ten miles off the coast of Hillsborough County, but there are fewer of them than there were last week.
Red tide algal blooms have also been observed in Pasco County.
Moderate concentrations were reported off the coast of Pinellas County in the past week, concentrations ranged from low to high along the coasts of Hillsborough County, from background concentrations to high concentrations in the counties of Manatee and Sarasota, from background concentrations to moderate concentrations in Charlotte County, and from background concentrations to high concentrations in the counties of Lee District and Collier County.
Respiratory symptoms are still reported in the Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier areas.
Over the past week, there have been no reports of respiratory symptoms in the northwest of Florida.
